result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffery A. Hanson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: To pay the costs of the action.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.  No presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores or any establishment whose primary purpose is the sale and/or consumption of alcohol.   Not to possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription and then take only in the amount and frequency prescribed.  Not to possess or use any drug paraphernalia.

Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments, including AODA assessment, as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment. Compliance with mental health treatment including taking of medications.    Defendant must have a DNA sample on file with the State of Wisconsin and pay a DNA surcharge.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court with attorney Tara L. Teesch.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Defendant apologizes to the court, makes statement. Bond is no longer in effect.
Copy of letter from defendant to ADA Korb.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file, reviews letter from defendant indicating what's been happening in his life the last 4 months. Defendant requests another 60 days to complete the community service. State objects, this case is over a year old, we need to see this matter concluded. Defendant would like time to retain an atty before proceeding with sentencing. Court indicates this is the last adjournment, needs to have atty in place by next hearing as sentencing will happen that day. Court encourages defendant to contact PD's regarding representation. State indicates offer is off the table. Bond remains in effect.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 28, 2017 at 08:00 am.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file.  State indicates defendant presented confirmation of some community service hours he's completed, requests 90 adjournment to give defendant more time to complete remainder of the community service. Court grants request.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 13, 2017 at 09:45 am.
Court lifts no contact with T.D.  Any contact is not to be at defendants house.

Defendant asks that court lift the no contact with T.D.  State expresses their concerns with lifting the no contact.  Court lifts the no contact with T.D. Any contact is not to be at defendants house.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file.  State indicates defendant has complied with most of the State's offer but needs a little more time to complete the community service. Defendant requests date in April to allow him time to complete community service. Bond remains in effect as amended.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 10, 2017 at 09:45 am.
Defendant requests to lift the no contact with T.D.  State expresses their concern with lifting of the no contact. Court not revising the bond, remains in effect as previously set.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea.  Defendant stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty. State asks court to set off sentencing for 6 months to allow defendant time to complete terms of their pretrial offer. Bond remains in effect.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 12, 2016 at 09:30 am.
from defendant apologizes for his actions.
To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center.  No contact direct or indirect with T.D.

Defendant Jeffery A. Hanson in court.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel.  Defendant wants to try to resolve matter with DA, waives right to Counsel.  Court questions Defendant, finds defendant competent to proceed, finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver.  Defendant to make appointment with DA.  Bond set.  Status conference scheduled for June 2, 2016 at 09:45 am.
